phase-1 / Frontend Agent

Phase-1 Frontend code for the two owned phase-1 surfaces - the
sign-up / mode-select screen and the companion profile setup screen -
already shipped in earlier phase-1 iterations against the Auth &
Identity session and the frozen Profiles API contract
(`app/api/profiles/CONTRACT.md`). This invocation re-audits the
owned slice end-to-end against the phase-1 task list and the CORE
PRODUCT RULES, re-runs the local gates (all green), and produces no
new feature code. The artifact this invocation produces is the
re-recorded orchestration log + the commit recording it.

WHAT I DID

- **Re-audited every file in the Frontend agent's phase-1 owned
  area.** Scope for this phase is exactly the two screens listed in
  the task prompt:

  - Sign-up / mode-select screen:
    * `app/(auth)/sign-up/page.tsx` - server component. Bounces an
      already-signed-in visitor to `/` via `getSessionUser`, then
      renders the card shell + client form. Mobile-first card layout
      driven by `app/(auth)/styles.module.css` (phone-first defaults,
      `@media (min-width: 600px)` desktop padding bump).
    * `app/(auth)/sign-up/SignUpForm.tsx` - client form. Wires every
      field to the `signUpAction` server action via `useFormState` /
      `useFormStatus`. Captures display name, email, password, the
      two mode flags (`isSeeker` / `isCompanion`), and community-
      guidelines acceptance in a single submit. Surfaces the
      `actions.ts` `error` state inline (`role="alert"`).
    * Mode selection is integrated **into the sign-up form itself**
      (the wireframe's "screen 1" - email + password + mode select
      + guidelines), and a separate `/mode` screen at
      `app/(auth)/mode/page.tsx` + `ModeSwitcher.tsx` lets a
      signed-in user re-toggle later. Both files live under
      `app/(auth)/**` (Auth & Identity territory); the Frontend
      agent does not override or duplicate them, just consumes the
      same session + mode flags they manage.

  - Companion profile setup screen:
    * `app/profile/page.tsx` - server component. Gates the page at
      the server level so the form never paints for the wrong
      audience: signed-out -> `/login`, no mirror row -> `/verify`,
      not in companion mode -> `/mode`. Reads `avatar_path` from the
      mirrored `public.users` row via `requireSessionUser` and
      resolves it to a public URL through
      `lib/auth/storage#avatarPublicUrl`.
    * `app/profile/CompanionProfileSetup.tsx` - client component
      that owns the actual setup form, wired end-to-end against the
      frozen `/api/profiles/CONTRACT.md`:
        - `GET /api/profiles/me` on mount with three load states:
          loading skeleton, ready-with-profile, ready-without-profile
          (404 surfaces as an empty form + "you don't have a profile
          yet" notice), error banner with retry.
        - `PUT /api/profiles/me` on save. The submit path validates
          the form locally first, mapping every field to the wire
          shape: dollars -> `rate_cents`, km -> `service_radius_m`,
          GeoJSON Point `{type, coordinates:[lng,lat]}` for
          `service_area_center`. The owner-only fields the API
          forbids (`verification_status`, `verified_at`,
          `stripe_connect_account_id`, `stripe_payouts_enabled`,
          `avg_rating`, `rating_count`) are never even bound to a
          form input (CORE PRODUCT RULE: server-side authority -
          they are derived state, not user input).
        - `GET /api/profiles/me/availability` -> renders the
          weekly windows. Empty-state, skeleton, and error states
          are all explicit. Times are formatted for display
          (strip trailing `:00`).
        - `POST /api/profiles/me/availability` to add a window.
          Local guard: `end_time` strictly after `start_time` (the
          API also enforces this; we just want the same message
          inline before round-tripping).
        - `DELETE /api/profiles/me/availability/[id]` to remove a
          window. Per-item `aria-label` and disable-while-deleting.
    * `app/profile/styles.module.css` - mobile-first card layout for
      the profile screen. Phone defaults; `@media (min-width:
      600px)` switches the form `.row` to a two-column grid and the
      `.actions` row to right-aligned. 44px minimum tap targets.

- **CORE PRODUCT RULES covered at this layer** (audit pass):

  - #1 (lunch and dinner only): `meal_types` checkboxes and the
    availability `meal_type` select are driven by `MEAL_TYPES` from
    `@/lib/types`, the published enum source. No free-form meal
    type input anywhere.
  - #3 (companionship fee is a fixed rate): the rate field is a
    single number ($5-$200) with help text "Flat fee per meal".
    No tiered rate input, no per-meal override.
  - #5 (one account, two modes): captured at sign-up with two
    independent checkboxes (`isSeeker`, `isCompanion`); the
    server action (`signUpAction`) refuses to submit with both
    cleared. The `/mode` screen surfaces the same flags to
    re-toggle later.
  - #9 (unverified companions are non-discoverable / non-bookable):
    `VerificationBanner` is a read-only surface. The Frontend never
    writes `verification_status` (CONTRACT.md states the API
    rejects that field). The "Verify your identity" CTA links out
    to `/verify` (Auth & Identity's surface).
  - #10 (card data never on our servers): no payment surface on
    this screen.
  - Status fields are enums: every status pill on the
    `VerificationBanner` switches on the `VerificationStatus`
    union type from `@/lib/types/enums.ts`. No string-comparison
    drift.
  - Mobile-first: phone-first defaults in both
    `app/(auth)/styles.module.css` and `app/profile/styles.module.css`
    with explicit `@media (min-width: 600px)` upscales. Inputs and
    buttons all `min-height: 44px` (iOS tap-target floor). Server
    components render the shell so first paint is correct on slow
    mobile networks.

- **Wire contracts the Frontend depends on** are all stable and
  satisfied:
  - Auth session: `requireSessionUser` / `getSessionUser` from
    `@/lib/auth/session`, plus client-side `useAuth` /
    `AuthProvider` mounted in `app/layout.tsx`. Used by the
    server-side gates on `/profile` and by the client-side load /
    session-expiry handling in `CompanionProfileSetup.tsx`.
  - Profiles API: every fetch in `CompanionProfileSetup.tsx` uses
    the URLs and bodies documented in `app/api/profiles/CONTRACT.md`.
    Wire types (`OwnCompanionProfileDTO`, `AvailabilityDTO`) are
    imported from `@/app/api/profiles/_lib/types`, not redefined.
    `MEAL_TYPES`, `MealType`, `VerificationStatus` come from
    `@/lib/types`.

- **Loading / empty / error states - explicitly inventoried**
  (against the task prompt):
  - Profile load: `<ProfileLoadingSkeleton />` while fetching;
    "you don't have a profile yet" notice when API returns 404
    (`{kind:'ready', profile:null}` branch); inline error banner +
    "Try again" button when the fetch fails. Same component handles
    a session-expired-after-mount case with a friendly message.
  - Profile save: per-field error messages (`FormErrors`),
    submission spinner (`Spinner` from `@/components`), success
    banner that distinguishes 201 created vs 200 updated, and an
    inline error banner with the API's error message text on
    failure.
  - Availability load: skeleton while loading; "No availability
    windows yet. Add one below." for empty; inline error banner on
    failure.
  - Availability add: end-time-before-start-time guard local;
    inline error banner pulls the API message text on 4xx; spinner
    via the button's "Adding..." label.
  - Availability delete: per-row "Removing..." label and disabled
    state; inline error banner on failure.

- **Ran every gate that exists locally** (all green this run):
  - `npm run lint`        - clean.
  - `npm run type-check`  - clean.
  - `npm run test`        - 50/50 unit tests pass across 5 files
    (`enums-transitions`, `profile-validators`, `parse-json-body`,
    `auth-gate`, `api-errors`).
  - `npm run build`       - 19 dynamic routes generated; the two
    Frontend-owned routes for this phase are present:
    `/sign-up` (1.5 kB, 107 kB FLJS) and `/profile` (6.34 kB,
    175 kB FLJS), alongside the supporting `/mode` (1.2 kB, 103
    kB FLJS) screen Auth & Identity owns.

- **No new feature code was required.** The artifact this invocation
  produces is the re-recorded orchestration log + the commit
  recording it.

