- **Push to git / deploy / modify secrets / provision cloud
  infrastructure.** Per the operating rules. Listed under MANUAL
  CHECKPOINTS.

INTERFACES PUBLISHED

The Frontend agent is a **consumer** of every published contract -
nothing is published outward from this slice this phase. For
reference, the contracts the Frontend consumes (already frozen):

- `app/api/profiles/CONTRACT.md` - Core API profiles wire contract
  (endpoints, status codes, error envelope, DTO shapes).
- `app/api/profiles/_lib/types.ts` - `OwnCompanionProfileDTO`,
  `PublicCompanionProfileDTO`, `AvailabilityDTO` (imported, not
  redefined).
- `@/lib/types` - `MEAL_TYPES`, `MealType`, `VerificationStatus`,
  `GeoJSONPoint` (imported, not redefined).
- `@/lib/auth` - `AuthProvider`, `useAuth` (client-side session).
- `@/lib/auth/session` - `requireSessionUser`, `getSessionUser`
  (server-side session gates).
- `@/lib/auth/storage` - `avatarPublicUrl` (server-side avatar URL
  resolution).

